quran[15]{c,v,t,f}:
  56,76,"And verily that is indeed a great oath, if you but know."
  56,77,"That (this) is indeed an honourable recitation (the Noble Qur’ân)."
  56,78,"In a Book well-guarded (with Allâh in the heaven i.e. Al-Lauh Al-Mahfûz )."
  67,16,"Do you feel secure that He, Who is over the heaven (Allâh), will not cause the earth to sink with you, and then it should quake?"
  67,17,"Or do you feel secure that He, Who is over the heaven (Allâh), will not send against you a violent whirlwind? Then you shall know how (terrible) has been My Warning."
  67,18,"And indeed those before them belied (the Messengers of Allâh), then how terrible was My denial (punishment)?"
  68,10,"And (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم) obey you not everyone Hallaf Mahîn (the one who swears much and is a liar or is worthless). [Tafsir At-Tabari]"
  68,11,"A slanderer, going about with calumnies,"
  68,12,"Hinderer of the good, transgressor, sinful,"
  69,7,"Which Allâh imposed on them for seven nights and eight days in succession, so that you could see men lying overthrown (destroyed), as if they were hollow trunks of date-palms!"
  69,8,"Do you see any remnants of them?"
  69,9,"And Fir‘aun (Pharaoh), and those before him, and the cities overthrown [the towns of the people of [Lût (Lot)] committed sin."
  70,1,"A questioner asked concerning a torment about to befall"
  70,2,"Upon the disbelievers, which none can avert,"
  70,3,"From Allâh, the Lord of the ways of ascent."